Great place for breakfast with generous portions.  Everything has been cooked correctly every time I've been to this restaurant. My personal favorite is the steak and eggs Mexican style.  If you order this breakfast dish and choose their big fluffy pancakes as your side, then you will will not likely be hungry again until evening. The seating is diner-style with some counter seats and small tables surrounding the grill area. Plan on separating into more than one table if you are in a group of more than 4 people. You can also pickup an order to go.

I called in an order this morning for the $9.99 Steak and Egg special to be told by the server who identified herself as Sam that they weren't running the special anymore.  She then offers a T-Bone for $12.99 with wheat toast and mixed fruit jelly.  So I order the T-bone and asked for it to be cooked medium rare.  As we arrive in the parking lot there's a huge sign with the steak special for $9.99.  I question her about it and she insist that the sign is old and they are not running the special anymore.  Then I show her the dry erase board over the cash register which clearly shows the special for $9.99.  I ask her when will the manager be in and at first she says an hour then she tries to pass the cook off as the manager.  However, there was a customer who said he is friends with Carlos the manager and that he will be there in an hour.  She leaves our food out in a bag sitting on the counter while she serves other customers.  I get to work and I have a well done touch piece of leather passed off for steak.  The food is cold. No jelly or serving utensils.  My friend was missing pico de gallo, jelly and serving utensils from her order.  The last time I was there (less than two weeks ago) the service was good and the food was perfect.  However, it's hard to mess up a veggie omelet. My experience today was horrible and due to the poor customer service I don't envision myself patronizing this establishment again. Manager off today but plan on speaking to him first thing in the morning when I return this poorly prepared breakfast. .  Update:  I gave them a third star because the follow-up with Carlos went well.  Carlos apologized for the bad experience I had and replaced my meal in it's entirety.  I appreciate his customer service and that he did not make excuses.
